project.title: Mortal Engines - London Weapons
project.description:
Concept art for the film Mortal Engines (2018) 
I ended up doing a heckuva lot of drawings for this film over a ten year period at Weta Workshop. This first batch is some of the designs for weapons that were to be seen in the city of London. There's a bunch more vehicles, characters and weapons that I'll post up on here soon.
Lotsa fun! Was cool seeing some of these get built by super skilled craftspeople!

project.title: Bison Anatomy Model for Artist
project.description:
Hey everyone !

New year new project. Finally took the time to finish my bison Anatomy model
Available here : https://gumroad.com/nicolasmorel?sort=page#josqC

Instagram : @nicolas_morel_art
Ready to use for Muscles simulation such as Ziva Dynamics.
He is optimized for riggers and Groomers who want to work on a personal project or sharpen their skills by practicing on a model with a vfx production quality.

But at an affordable price. This include clean topology especially for Face Shapes. And clean uvs and textures.

He is the Result of my of experience as a Senior creature Modeler in big studios such as MPC, One of Us, Ziva Dynamics, Axis Studios and other smaller companies.

project.title: Feng
project.description:
Here is Feng my ongoing project, I hope to post soon the rest of it !
She is actually a rework of an old character I created with a teammate 2 years ago, therefore the process was different from usual. 
Feng is the right arm of a powerful asian mafia in a near futur and hides her identity/occupation; I had fun making those 2 outfits accordingly and go out of my comfort zone with some streetwear or regular non fantasy fashion ! I really want to show other aspects of this character  as well as the process sketches very soon !

project.title: Panam Palmer
project.description:
Some concepts of Panam Palmer, cyberpunk queen of the desert. It's so fun to work on such a charismatic NPC!  

Her hair was an especially tricky subject, we had dozens of iterations of it. Finally, she got a characteristic bun, designed by our art director and character team lead - Pawe Mielniczuk. And it looks great, I can't imagine her now without it. ;)

Art direction: Pawe Mielniczuk

project.title: Downtown West Modular Pack - UE4
project.description:
Downtown West Modular Pack is a UE4 project created by PurePolygons with the collaboration of 6 artists in total. The pack will be available for free indefinitely on the Unreal Marketplace and can be downloaded and used by anyone within the Unreal Engine. 
(Link Coming Soon)

Downtown West realizes the look of a classic mid-western style outdoor shopping street in the United States. With colorful store fronts, rich foliage, and inviting surroundings.

Myself: Art Direction, Concept, World Building, Asset Creation, Texture Creation, UE4 Materials /Blueprints, Lighting, Trees / Grass, all of the Modular Ground Work, and various other works to bring the project together
The Team:

project.title: Khedemar- Prophet's Respite
project.description: The stepwells of Prophets Respite; an ethereal plane that the Prophets of Khedemar head to when gathering power and formulating thoughts. This is a meditation chamber of sorts where the thoughts of all beings are shared, where one mind merges with another, and all ideas become one. This concept is reflected in the seemingly neverending stepwells of this world, with infinite areas to descend into. The last frames show the threads of life, inactive and active, as they start to bind materials together.
